The paper deals with scheduling in the cellular uplink, which is a problem in wireless communication networks. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the practical constraints imposed in the 3GPP LTE-A standard, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper proposes approximation algorithms, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
